# Development Tools Documentation Auto-Reference

When configuring development tools, **ALWAYS reference the appropriate indexed documentation** using @ mentions:

## Cursor IDE
- Use **@Cursor Rules** when:
  - Creating new `.mdc` rule files
  - Configuring rule types (Always, Auto Attached, Agent Requested, Manual)
  - Setting up glob patterns
  - Organizing nested rules
  - Understanding rule anatomy

- Use **@Cursor API** when:
  - Working with Cursor's API
  - Integrating external tools
  - Building extensions

- Use **@Cursor Learn** when:
  - Learning Cursor features
  - Understanding AI capabilities
  - Optimizing workflow

## Turbopack (Next.js Dev Server)
- Use **@turbopack** when:
  - Configuring development server
  - Setting up filesystem caching
  - Optimizing build performance
  - Troubleshooting build issues
  - Configuring custom loaders

## Storybook (Component Development)
- Use **@storybook** when:
  - Setting up Storybook configuration
  - Creating stories
  - Configuring addons
  - Setting up testing utilities
  - Building component documentation

## Validation (Zod)
- Use **@https://zod.dev** when:
  - Creating validation schemas
  - Parsing and validating data
  - TypeScript type inference
  - Error handling
  - Schema composition

